        <prompt>What were "scalawags" during Reconstruction?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Southern whites who supported Republican policies</option>
            <option letter="b">Northern migrants to the South</option>
            <option letter="c">Former Confederate soldiers</option>
            <option letter="d">African American politicians</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>Scalawags were white Southerners who supported Republican Reconstruction policies and often cooperated with freedmen and carpetbaggers, earning them contempt from other Southern whites.</explanation>
