    <question>
        <prompt>What was the significance of the Tenure of Office Act of 1867?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Required Senate approval for removal of cabinet members</option>
            <option letter="b">Limited presidential terms to four years</option>
            <option letter="c">Established requirements for federal judges</option>
            <option letter="d">Created new cabinet positions</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>The Tenure of Office Act restricted the president's power to remove cabinet members without Senate approval, leading to conflict between Congress and President Johnson.</explanation>
